==English==

===Etymology===
From {{prefix|be|wilder}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/bɪˈwɪldə(ɹ)/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/bɪˈwɪldəɹ/|lang=en}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To [[confuse]], [[puzzle]] or [[befuddle]] someone, especially with many different things.
#: ''All the different possible options may '''bewilder''' us.''
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To [[disorientate]] someone.
#: ''Don't push me into that maze and '''bewilder''' me.''

